  "doc_id": "20684",
  "text": "For data collection, a single crystal was first immersed into a cryo-protectant consisting of 17% glycerol and 83% reservoir solution for ~30 s. The crystal was then mounted on a nylon loop and flash-cooled in a nitrogen gas stream at 100 K. X-ray data were in-house collected using a Rigaku rotating copper anode equipped with an R-axis image plate. The diffraction images were processed with HKL2000 [CITATION_1] . The initial model of the SS2 enolase was built by molecular replacement using the program MOLREP (Vagin and Teplyakov, 1997) with the structure of its homologous protein from S. pneumoniae as a search model (PDB code 1W6T). The structure was completed using alternate cycles of manual building in COOT [CITATION_2] and refinement using REFMAC5 [CITATION_3] as implemented in the CCP4 suite (collaborative., 1994) and Phenix.refine [CITATION_4] . The stereo-chemical quality of the final model was assessed by Procheck [CITATION_5] . The final coordinates and its related structural factors were deposited into the RCSB Protein Data Bank with the accession number of 4EWJ. The final statistics for data collection and structural refinement are summarized in Table 1 .",
